A 31-year-old suspect is set to appear at the Roodepoort Magistrate's Court in connection with Tshegofatso Pule's murder. One of the community members, who found her lifeless body in a veld in Durban Deep, says this has left him traumatised. Courtesy #DStv403   JOHANNESBURG - A 31-year-old man accused of the brutal murder of Tshegofatso Pule abandoned his bid for bail. The body of the heavily pregnant woman, was found hanging from a tree in an open field in the Durban Deep area, earlier this month. WATCH: Funeral service of Tshegofatso Pule Muzikayise Malephane was arrested and appeared in court earlier Wednesday. He was charged with one count of premeditated murder.